\f3 Grey Water (GW) and Black Water (BW) are collected in the ship\'92s Holding Tank.\
When the filling level reaches a predefined level, the sewage treatment starts auto-\
matically.\
The Feeding P/P starts to operate and is protected from running dry by process water.\
The pump conveys the raw sewage from the ship\'92s Holding Tank via the Macerator to\
the Saturator. The Macerator in the suction line reduces the solids in the raw sewage\
to 1 mm pieces.\
The sewage is enriched with air under a pressure of 5 bar. The Press. Sensor for Satu-\
rator measures this pressure in the Saturator. The defined pressure in the Saturator is\
controlled by the Press. Release Valve.\
Treatment process\
The sewage enriched with air is discharged from the Saturator through the Press. Re-\
lease Valve and loses the pressure. The excess air forms bubbles. A flocculant is add-\
ed.\
Flocculant and air bubbles connect to the suspended particles of the sewage and\
form larger flakes in the Flotation TK. This reduces the total density: Flakes, particles and\
other impurities are lifted out through buoyancy. This creates a sludge foam on the sur-\
face of the Flotation TK. and leaves the clear phase in the lower part of the Flotation TK.\
The Clear Phase P/P operates throughout a predefined period to maintain the oper-\
ation level in the Flotation TK. Then, the Clear Phase P/P stops. This allows fluid and\
sludge foam to build up in the Flotation TK. The sludge foam spills over the brim of the\
Flotation TK. into the Sludge Compartment.\
