When the sludge foam in the Sludge Compartment reaches the Level Sensor Sludge\
Flotation Tk., the Sludge P/P starts to operate. This pump conveys the sludge from the\
Sludge Compartment to the ship\'92s Sludge Tank. The Cleaning Injector/Nozzle Flotation\
Tk. in the upper area cleans the Sludge Compartment.\
At the same time, the Clear Phase P/P starts to operate again to maintain the opera-\
tion level. The cycle in the Flotation TK. begins again. The Level Sensor Flotation Tk. pre-\
vents the Clear Phase P/P from running dry.\
The particles collected in the sump of the Flotation TK. can be drained manually via\
opening the 3-way Valve Sludge.\
UV Disinfection\
The Clear Phase P/P conveys the clear phase from the lower part of the Flotation TK.\
through the UV-Disinfection Plant 1. The clear phase passes through the UV lamps. The\
emitted UV light degrades the DNA of bacteria and microorganisms which renders\
the bacteria and microorganisms incapable of reproducing and infecting.\
The treated effluent is safe to discharge overboard.\
Inactivity / Switch off\
When the filling level of the ship\'91s Holding Tank falls below a defined stop level, the\
Sewage Treatment Plant enters the standby mode:\
\'96 The Macerator and the Feeding P/P stop.\
\'96 The Clear Phase P/P continues to operate until the Flotation TK. has been\
drained to its stop level.\
\'96 Then, the pressure of the Saturator is released. The liquid filling level of the Satu-\
rator is drained into the Flotation TK..\
\'96 All pumps stop operating and the Sewage Treatment Plant is in the standby\
mode.\
The plant remains in the standby mode until the filling level of the Holding Tank reach-\
es the start level.\
When the Sewage Treatment Plant is shut down via the touch panel, the plant carries\
out the steps to enter the standby mode.\
